## IntelliJ (technically CLion) settings for Rust programming.
(todo: figure out how to sync these *to the cloud* somehow)

Can always get a fresh config with:
    double-shift + "Restore default settings"

Plugins
- Rust
- IdeaVim

Keymap
- Alt-Z  toggle Zen mode
- Ctrl-Enter  Run
- Ctrl+-  Descrease font size
- Ctrl+=  Increase font size

Misc
- disable view main menu
- disable show intention bulb
- disable all inline hints (Settings > Editor > Inlay Hints)
- bump up the editor font size from 13 to 15 or 16 (25 for parents' tv)
- disable Editor > General > Gutter > Highlight modified lines in the gutter
- Editor > General > Appearence > disable caret blinking
- Editor > General > Mouse Control: Change font size with Ctrl+Mouse Whele in: All editors

Settings > Editor > Color Scheme > General > Errors and Warnings
- disable effects for:
    - Error
    - Warning
    - Weak warning
    - Unused symbol
    - Unknown symbol
    - typo
- and disable effects for General > Editor > caret row
